# Example additions for Raspberry Pi 5 + Waveshare 2-CH CAN HAT (MCP2515, SPI0).
# On Ubuntu 24.04 for Pi: /boot/firmware/config.txt
#
# Target HAT: Waveshare 2-CH CAN HAT (Amazon B087RJ6XGG)
#   - 2x MCP2515 + SN65HVD230, 16 MHz oscillator, SPI0 (CE0 + CE1)
#   - INT_0 = GPIO 23, INT_1 = GPIO 25 (default solder pads)
#   - Wiki: https://www.waveshare.com/wiki/2-CH_CAN_HAT
#
# If you have the 2-CH CAN HAT+ (B0C6LJQ...) instead, it is MCP2515 on SPI1
# with INT_0=GPIO22 / INT_1=GPIO13 — overlays differ, see:
#   https://www.waveshare.com/wiki/2-CH_CAN_HAT+

# Uncomment below to enable CAN on the base 2-CH CAN HAT:
# dtparam=spi=on
# dtoverlay=mcp2515-can0,oscillator=16000000,interrupt=23
# dtoverlay=mcp2515-can1,oscillator=16000000,interrupt=25
